FBIS4-11547 "drlat083_a_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-083 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba U.S. Government Authorizes Telephone Service U.S. Government Authorizes Telephone Service FL2604164094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 GMT 26 Apr 94 FL2604164094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] The U.S. Government has authorized the company IDB Worldcom to provide direct telex and telephone service between Cuba and the United States. (Mike Tower), the company's vice president, said that Havana will be paid its share of this commercial transaction, as authorized by Washington.
